$interpreted: Pang: These stone tablets I keep seeing... what do the carvings mean?
Naya: No idea what's written on those rocks. They were  already here when I was assigned to the prairie.
Tica: Hehe~ If big sis really wants to know, ask the expert. He studies Life Magic.
Tica: Prairie stone tablets are a major part of his research.
Pang: Research?
Tica: Comrade Pang is an outsider indeed! Not up to date with the latest news in the Kingdom, are we?
Tica: Here's a quick intro... for dummies!
Tica: The Rune Academy's separated into two schools of thought: Life Magic and Applied Magic.
Tica: Life Magic scholars are always rambling on about the next scientific breaktrough. They're always conducting strange experiments on campus...
Tica: They've contributed lots to the field of medicine though!
Naya: Which faculty do you belong to?
Tica: The Headmaster and I both study rune devices in the field of Applied Magic!
Tica: Naya's bow uses technology developed by my Academy!
Pang: Hey, watch it!
Tica: Hehehe~ Don't go crying to mommy!
Pang: There is wisdom in silence...

Naya: Even Boomshrooms are making a fuss.
What's going on here!?
Tica: Not to worry! Just watch your step; as long as you don't tread on them, you'll be fine!
Pang: Practice what you preach.

Tica: Baby don't worry, 'bout a thing, 
'cause every little thing, gonna be alright~
Naya: ...Didn't you just say?!
Tica: NO FAIR! It was HIS fault! HE bumped into me!
Pang: Shhhhhh! They're coming!
Tica: Perfect! Road block cleared; follow me!
Pang: YOU! In the middle!
Naya: I'm taking the rear. I've got my eyes on you.
